Titolo: Blue Max 2001

Anno: 1984

Descrizione: Blue Max 2001 is a diagonally-scrolling shooter written by Bob Polin (also credited as Rob Polin) for the Atari 8-bit family and published by Synapse Software in 1984. A Commodore 64 version was released the same year. Blue Max 2001 is the sequel to 1983's Blue Max, also by Polin, with the player piloting a futuristic hovercraft instead of a World War I biplane. Critics generally found the game disappointing compared with the original.

Genere: Scrolling shooter

Valutazione: N/A
